idlewatch-agent

Usage:
  idlewatch-agent [quickstart] [--dry-run] [--once] [--help]

Options:
  quickstart  Run first-run enrollment wizard and generate secure env config
  --dry-run   Collect and print one telemetry sample, then exit without Firebase writes
  --once      Collect and publish one telemetry sample, then exit
  --help      Show this help message

Environment:
  IDLEWATCH_HOST                     Optional custom host label (default: hostname)
  IDLEWATCH_INTERVAL_MS              Sampling interval in ms (default: 10000)
  IDLEWATCH_LOCAL_LOG_PATH           Optional NDJSON file path for local sample durability
  IDLEWATCH_OPENCLAW_USAGE           OpenClaw usage lookup mode: auto|off (default: auto)
  IDLEWATCH_OPENCLAW_PROBE_TIMEOUT_MS OpenClaw command timeout per probe in ms (default: 2500)
  IDLEWATCH_OPENCLAW_PROBE_RETRIES   Extra OpenClaw probe sweep retries after first pass (default: 1)
  IDLEWATCH_USAGE_STALE_MS           Mark OpenClaw usage stale beyond this age in ms (default: max(interval*3,60000))
  IDLEWATCH_USAGE_NEAR_STALE_MS      Mark OpenClaw usage as aging beyond this age in ms (default: floor((stale+grace)*0.85))
  IDLEWATCH_USAGE_STALE_GRACE_MS     Extra grace window before status becomes stale (default: min(interval,10000))
  IDLEWATCH_USAGE_REFRESH_REPROBES   Forced uncached reprobes when usage crosses stale threshold (default: 1)
  IDLEWATCH_USAGE_REFRESH_DELAY_MS   Delay between forced stale-threshold reprobes in ms (default: 250)
  IDLEWATCH_USAGE_REFRESH_ON_NEAR_STALE Trigger refresh when usage is near-stale: 1|0 (default: 1)
  IDLEWATCH_USAGE_IDLE_AFTER_MS      Downgrade stale usage alerts to idle notice beyond this age in ms (default: 21600000)
  IDLEWATCH_OPENCLAW_LAST_GOOD_MAX_AGE_MS  Reuse last successful usage snapshot after probe failures up to this age in ms
  IDLEWATCH_OPENCLAW_LAST_GOOD_CACHE_PATH Persist/reuse last successful usage snapshot across restarts (default: os tmp dir)
  IDLEWATCH_REQUIRE_FIREBASE_WRITES  Require Firebase publish path in --once mode: 1|0 (default: 0)
  FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID                Firebase project id
  FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_FILE      Path to service account JSON file (preferred for production)
  FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON      Raw JSON service account (supported, less secure than file path)
  FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_B64       Base64-encoded JSON service account (legacy)
  FIRESTORE_EMULATOR_HOST            Optional Firestore emulator host; allows local writes without service-account creds

